ubmission interface — minimal ring buffer, no proprietary driver\n124:- [ ] WS9-07 MMIO register map for target GPU compute dispatch (start with virtio-gpu or simple compute)\n125:- [ ] WS9-08 Book of Truth hooks: log every DMA mapping, every GPU command, every MMIO write\n126:- [ ] WS9-09 GPU compute shader/kernel format — simple dispatachable compute tasks\n127:- [ ] WS9-10 Matmul offload: move quantized matrix multiply to GPU, keep results in GPU partition\n128:- [ ] WS9-11 Attention score computation offload to GPU\n129:- [ ] WS9-12 GPU error handling: timeout, hang detection, forced reset, logged to Book of Truth\n130:- [ ] WS9-13 Benchmark: GPU vs CPU inference speed for TinyLlama 1.1B Q4_0\n131:- [ ] WS9-14 Fallback: if no IOMMU available, GPU disabled entirely — CPU-only mode, no exceptions\n133:### WS10 — Multi-Architecture Model Support\n134:- [ ] WS10-01 Abstract forward pass interface — model-agnostic layer dispatch\n135:- [ ] WS10-02 Mistral architecture support (sliding window attention, different GQA config)\n136:- [ ] WS10-03 Qwen2 architecture support (different FFN layout, tied embeddings)\n137:- [ ] WS10-04 Phi-3 architecture support (different attention pattern, block structure)\n138:- [ ] WS10-05 Architecture auto-detection from GGUF metadata keys\n139:- [ ] WS10-06 Model registry: map GGUF architecture string to forward pass implementation\n141:### WS11 — Extended Quantization Support\n142:- [ ] WS11-01 Q5_0 and Q5_1 quantization (5-bit, wider dynamic range)\n143:- [ ] WS11-02 Q2_K, Q3_K, Q4_K, Q5_K, Q6_K (k-quant family, mixed precision)\n144:- [ ] WS11-03 IQ quantization formats (importance-based, variable bit-width per weight)\n145:- [ ] WS11-04 Quantization format auto-selection from GGUF tensor type field\n146:- [ ] WS11-05 Performance comparison matrix: tok/s vs quantization level vs model size\n148:### WS12 — Model Conversion & Preparation Tooling (Host-Side)\n151:- [ ] WS12-01 GGUF model validator — verify file integrity, tensor checksu